  "title": "PRIMADONNA",
  "description": "When Daisy Donna, the most famous pop star in the world, vanishes from public life, her estranged sister turns to Daisy’s legion of obsessed fans to try and find her. This parasocial thriller attempts to unravel the true story of this missing prima donna.",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Liam Witte<br><strong>Director</strong>: Abby Witte<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Kate Boswell, Avery Nault, Mariana Perri<br/><strong>Designers</strong>: Kate Boswell, Andraya Diogo &amp; Avery Nault<br/><strong>Stage Manager</strong>: Kate Elliott<br/></br>",
  "website": "https://instagram.com/littlesisco_",
  "plain_language": "PRIMADONNA is about a famous pop star named Daisy Donna who goes missing right before starting her world tour. Her younger sister Marisol, who she hasn't spoken to in years, tries to find her by turning to Daisy's overly-dedicated online fan base. However, as dark secrets about the past are revealed, Marisol has to deal with her family's history and her sister's fame if she is going to find out what happened to Daisy.",
